A MAN will appear in court after cops bust him with drugs on Monday. He was arrested after police spotted a suspicious-looking Toyota Tazz with dark windows in the Welkom CBD, Free State. Captain Stephen Thakeng said: “A 31-year-old suspect was arrested and held at Welkom Police Station. “He was charged with possession of drugs after reaction team members noticed three suspicious men climbing into a blue Toyota Tazz with dark windows. “Police found four balls of nyaope hidden in one of the men’s private parts and cash amounting to R320. “He will appear in the Welkom Magistrates Court soon.” Welkom cluster commander Major-General Lerato Molale thanked the police for working hard to keep the Welkom CBD drug free.